ShareOverviewSummaryBarclays Capital Inc. has worked on four contracts worth $7.07 million USD in obligations from the federal government since FY2007. In its latest active fiscal year (2013), the organization received a total of -$2.07 million USD in obligations.The principal agencies it has contracted with are the Department of Labor and Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation.* A negative obligation amount is a de-obligation, meaning the money was given back to the federal government.

